Usually, lecture conflicts are fine as long as you talk with course staff to ensure that you don't have conflicting final exam times. As a side note, why are you taking both 61A and 88? They count for the same requirements and heavily overlap

---------

You cannot get credit (check cs88 listing) for both cs88 and cs61a (you wouldn't want to take both anyway they are the same course content except 61a adds a little SQL and scheme).

As a warning though, not all courses offer alterate final exams even if there is a conflict so definitely check with the professors.
